Title: All Lives Matter T-Shirt
Body (HTML):
In an awful tragedy occurred in Chapel Hill, North Carolina. Deah Barakat, 23; his wife, Yusor Mohammad, 21; and her sister, Razan Mohammad Abu-Salha, 19; were murdered.

It seems every time we turn on our televisions there has been a new tragedy. 3 lives were taken, 3 futures ended, and for what? This needs to end. No matter what race or religion you are - we are all humans, and all of our lives matter.

Before he died, Deah had set up a fundraising page raising money to provide dental care to Syrian children made refugees by the country??s civil war. To honor the lives of Deah, Yusor, and Razan, we have decided to release Limited Edition All Lives Matter T-Shirts, and all proceeds will be donated to Deah??s Syrian Dental Relief Fund.
